---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Privacy Policy - Caipi">
  <!-- Navigation -->
  <nav class="fixed top-0 left-0 right-0 z-50 px-6 md:px-12 py-6 flex justify-between items-center" style="background: linear-gradient(to bottom, var(--background) 0%, transparent 100%);">
    <a href="/" class="flex items-center gap-2 font-semibold text-lg tracking-tight text-foreground">
      <span class="w-2 h-2 bg-primary rounded-full" style="box-shadow: 0 0 12px var(--primary);"></span>
      Caipi
    </a>
    <div class="flex items-center gap-6 md:gap-10">
      <a href="/#features" class="hidden md:inline text-sm font-medium text-muted-foreground hover:text-foreground transition-colors">Features</a>
      <a href="/#pricing" class="hidden md:inline text-sm font-medium text-muted-foreground hover:text-foreground transition-colors">Pricing</a>
      <a href="/#pricing" class="bg-foreground text-background px-4 py-2 rounded-md font-semibold text-sm hover:bg-primary hover:text-background transition-all">
        Download
      </a>
    </div>
  </nav>

  <main class="pt-32 pb-16 px-4 md:px-8">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-foreground mb-2">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="text-muted-foreground mb-12">Last updated: January 2026</p>

      <div class="space-y-8 text-foreground/90">
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground mb-4">Overview</h2>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
            Caipi is designed with privacy in mind. The application runs entirely on your local machine,
            and we collect minimal data necessary to provide and improve our service.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground mb-4">Who We Are</h2>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
            The data controller for Caipi is Paul-Louis Pröve (Germany). You can reach us at
            <a href="mailto:caipi@plpp.de" class="text-primary hover:underline">caipi@plpp.de</a>.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground mb-4">Data We Collect</h2>

          <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-foreground mt-6 mb-3">Purchase Information</h3>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
            When you purchase Caipi, our payment processor collects:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mt-2 space-y-1 text-muted-foreground">
            <li>Email address (for license delivery and support)</li>
            <li>Payment information (processed securely by our payment provider)</li>
            <li>Country (for tax compliance)</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-foreground mt-6 mb-3">License Validation</h3>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
            When you activate your license, we verify it with our licensing service. This sends:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mt-2 space-y-1 text-muted-foreground">
            <li>Your license key</li>
            <li>A device identifier (hashed, non-reversible)</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-foreground mt-6 mb-3">Update Checks</h3>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
            Caipi periodically checks for updates (for example via GitHub Releases). This sends a request
            containing your current version number. Like any web request, the services involved may also
            receive technical data such as your IP address and user agent, which is used only for basic
            security and troubleshooting.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground mb-4">Data We Do NOT Collect</h2>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mt-2 space-y-1 text-muted-foreground">
            <li>Your conversations with Claude</li>
            <li>Your files or file contents</li>
            <li>Commands you run</li>
            <li>Usage analytics or telemetry</li>
            <li>Browsing history or behavior tracking</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-3 text-muted-foreground">
            All interactions with Claude go directly from your device to Anthropic's servers.
            We never see or store this data.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground mb-4">Third-Party Services</h2>

          <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-foreground mt-6 mb-3">Anthropic (Claude)</h3>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
            Caipi uses Claude Code, which connects to Anthropic's servers. Your conversations and
            data sent to Claude are governed by
            <a href="https://www.anthropic.com/privacy" class="text-primary hover:underline">Anthropic's Privacy Policy</a>.
          </p>

          <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-foreground mt-6 mb-3">GitHub</h3>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
            Software updates are distributed via GitHub Releases. See
            <a href="https://docs.github.com/en/site-policy/privacy-policies/github-privacy-statement" class="text-primary hover:underline">GitHub's Privacy Statement</a>.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground mb-4">Legal Bases (GDPR)</h2>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
            Where GDPR applies, we process personal data based on: performance of a contract (to deliver and
            maintain your license), compliance with legal obligations (tax/accounting), and legitimate interests
            (basic security and support).
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground mb-4">Your Rights (GDPR)</h2>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">If you are in the European Union, you have the right to:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mt-2 space-y-1 text-muted-foreground">
            <li>Access your personal data</li>
            <li>Correct inaccurate data</li>
            <li>Request deletion of your data</li>
            <li>Request restriction of processing</li>
            <li>Object to processing of your data</li>
            <li>Data portability</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-3 text-muted-foreground">
            To exercise these rights, contact us at
            <a href="mailto:caipi@plpp.de" class="text-primary hover:underline">caipi@plpp.de</a>.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3 text-muted-foreground">
            You also have the right to lodge a complaint with your local supervisory authority.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground mb-4">Data Retention</h2>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
            We retain purchase records and license information for as long as your license is valid
            and for a reasonable period thereafter for legal and accounting purposes. You may request
            deletion of your data at any time.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground mb-4">Cookies</h2>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
            We do not use tracking cookies on our website. Our site may use essential cookies required for basic
            functionality.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground mb-4">Security</h2>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
            We implement appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect your data.
            All communications use HTTPS encryption. We do not store sensitive payment information —
            this is handled entirely by our payment provider.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground mb-4">Changes to This Policy</h2>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
            We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of significant
            changes via email or through the Software. Your continued use after changes constitutes
            acceptance of the updated policy.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground mb-4">Contact</h2>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
            For privacy-related questions or to exercise your rights, contact us at
            <a href="mailto:caipi@plpp.de" class="text-primary hover:underline">caipi@plpp.de</a>.
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-12 pt-8 border-t border-border">
        <a href="/" class="text-sm text-primary hover:underline">← Back to home</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>

  <!-- Footer -->
  <footer class="py-12 px-4 md:px-8 border-t border-border">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto flex flex-col md:flex-row justify-between items-center gap-6">
      <div class="text-muted-foreground text-sm">© 2025 Caipi. Built with care.</div>
      <div class="flex items-center gap-8">
        <a href="/terms" class="text-muted-foreground text-sm hover:text-foreground transition-colors">Terms</a>
        <a href="/privacy" class="text-foreground text-sm">Privacy</a>
        <a href="/refund" class="text-muted-foreground text-sm hover:text-foreground transition-colors">Refund Policy</a>
        <a href="mailto:caipi@plpp.de" class="text-muted-foreground text-sm hover:text-foreground transition-colors">Contact</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </footer>
</Layout>
